==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Greek]] [[πατριωτικός]] (''patriotikos'').

===Adjective===

'''patriotic'''

#Inspired by [[patriotism]]; actuated by love of one's [[country]]; [[zealously]] and unselfishly [[devote]]d to the [[service]] of one's country; as, a patriotic statesman, vigilance.

==== Quotations ====

*'''1885''' — [[w:Gilbert and Sullivan|Gilbert & Sullivan]], ''[[s:The_Mikado|The Mikado]]''
*:But if '''patriotic''' sentiment is wanted,
*:I've '''patriotic''' ballads cut and dried;
*:For where'er our country's banner may be planted,
*:All other local banners are defied!

==== Translations ====
*French: [[patriotique]]

